{"ts":"2026-05-31T05:42:14.222Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-q4zx"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Runtime-resolved shell completion for custom statuses/types via helper command"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Follow-up to pm-jtdc (MCP status enum made config-driven 2026-05-31). Shell completion (completion.ts) still emits a static script using DEFAULT_STATUS_VALUES / DEFAULT_ITEM_TYPES, so bash/zsh/fish completion of --status/--type never surfaces project-defined custom statuses/types. This does NOT block agents (completion only suggests; the CLI accepts custom values), so it is low priority. Plan: add a `pm completion-statuses` / `pm completion-types` helper (mirroring the existing dynamic `pm completion-tags`) that prints the runtime-resolved status/type ids, and have the generated completion scripts call it for dynamic suggestions, falling back to the static defaults when unavailable."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Chore"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":4},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["completion","config-driven","schema"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-05-31T05:42:14.222Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-05-31T05:42:14.222Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"1a73d8c3a7e96f0631e399e133069a47c156ab48772fcf914de5f50ba2370280","message":""}
